<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - FUEL INJECTION PUMP - FUEL INJECTION PUMP - INSTALLATION OF NEW
        "SWITCHLESS" ELECTRIC SHUT-OFF SOLENOID
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSTALLATION OF NEW "SWITCHLESS" ELECTRIC SHUT-OFF SOLENOID</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4151146">11.46</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            .
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble solenoid and bracket assembly onto the inboard injection pump mounting studs.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Working from beneath the vehicle, hold the solenoid bracket firmly against the pump mounting
                flange and install the inboard washers and nuts by hand. Once in place, use a 14.2 mm (9/16 in.) swivel
                socket with a five inch extension and tighten injection pump mounting bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the metri-pack connector to the wiring harness.</para>
            <figure id="ef4151146" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg14479" filename="../figcg1/CG14479.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11.46. Solenoid Installation for PES6A Injection Pump.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
